r Bill Viola. Am Beispiel etwa von Teresa Hubbard/Alexander Birchler, Stan Douglas und Björn Melhus wird zudem eine umfassende Typologie künstlerischer Strategien in Film- und Videoloops entwickelt.  aThe history of film and video loops is at the same time a history of the mutual influence of artistic experiments, technical capabilities and the development of the history of exhibitions. Franziska Stöhr's comprehensive study analyzes decisive exhibitions such as »Information« (MoMA, New York, 1970), »Prospect 71: Projection« (Kunsthalle Düsseldorf, 1971) and »documenta 5-10« (1972-1997), with examples of works from artists such as Bruce Nauman, Dennis Oppenheim, Paul Sharits or Bill Viola. In addition, with the example of Teresa Hubbard/Alexander Birchler, Stan Douglas and Björn Melhus, a comprehensive typology of artistic strategies in film and video loops is developed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAusstellungsgeschichte. 4aBild. 4aFilm. 4aFilmkunst. 4aKunst. 4aKunstgeschichte. 4aKunstwissenschaft. 4aMedienkunst. 4aMuseumswissenschaft. 4aTechnikgeschichte. 4aVideo. 4aVideokunst. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aArt History.  aArt.  aExhibition Art.  aFilm Art.  aFilm.  aFine Arts.  aHistory of Technology.  aImage.  aMedia Art.  aMuseology.  aVideo Art.  aVideo.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2016z9783110482812oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB